  "rationale": "trigger_scan takes only Query parameters — no JSON body required. From a browser's perspective this is a CORS *simple* request (POST + no custom headers + no body), so a cross-origin attacker page can fire it without preflight. The bearer can ride along in `?token=` (router.rs:132), which a victim's referrer/history may already have leaked. Result: any page the operator visits while logged in can spam scans (DoS via runaway repo clone/sandbox spin) or, against a misconfigured repo, force scan paths the operator did not initiate. Same shape applies to /quarantine/:id/promote and /quarantine/:id/dismiss. Static pass missed because the CSRF surface is the *absence* of (a) CorsLayer with credential-aware policy, (b) Origin/Sec-Fetch-Site checks, (c) anti-CSRF token — all missing controls.",
